 10/1/2017 is 4.276% For more information regarding the Federal Direct Student Loan fees please visit the Federal Student Aid website. What is a student loan? A loan is borrowed money that must be repaid with interest. Direct Loan program The University of North Texas participates in the William D. Ford Federal Direct Loan program which allows you to borrow loan funds directly from the U.S. Department of Education. This program will give you and your parents a more stable, streamlined, and predictable borrowing experience.  It is important that you understand that a loan is a legal financial obligation, with interest, that you will be responsible for repaying. If you decide to borrow loans, we encourage you to be a responsible borrower and know the terms and conditions of your loans. Read the FAQs about the Direct Loan program. Types of Loans Federal Direct Loan (Subsidized) Direct Loan (Unsubsidized) Direct Loan Parent (PLUS) Direct Loan Grad PLUS Federal Perkins Loan Compare Federal Loan Programs State Texas B-On-Time (BOT) Loan Private/Alternative Private/Alternative Loan information Other Loans available from the Student Accounting Office Loans available from the Student Money Management Center Contact Us: Student Financial Aid and Scholarships 1155 Union Circle #311370 Denton, TX 76203-5017 USA Voice: 940-565-2302 Fax: 940-565-2738 Visit Us: Student Financial Aid & Scholarships 1147 Union Circle Eagle Student Services Center (ESSC), Rm 228 Denton, TX 76203 Hours: 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM, Monday - Friday Extended hours information can be found here. http://financialaid.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions on content or technical issues? Please contact us. financialaid@unt.edu UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on April 4, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness Select LanguageEnglishSpanish 